Colibri Engine Attribution
===========================

The local inference engine in Sawyer SuperC is derived from Colibri
(https://github.com/JustVugg/colibri) by Vincenzo / JustVugg.

Original license: Apache License 2.0
https://github.com/JustVugg/colibri/blob/main/LICENSE

Key components derived from Colibri:
- c/glm.c: GLM-5.2 MoE forward pass, MLA attention, DSA sparse attention
- int8/int4 integer-dot kernels (AVX2 maddubs)
- MTP speculative decoding (int8 draft head)
- Expert streaming from disk with per-layer LRU cache
- MLA weight absorption for decode
- KV-cache persistence
- Grammar-forced speculative drafts
- Byte-level BPE tokenizer

Colibri is used under the Apache 2.0 License with gratitude.
The Colibri project proved that a 744B MoE model can run on consumer
hardware by streaming experts from disk -- the foundational insight
that makes SuperC possible.